{
  "stem": "24268.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Our-- what our home-- we had a administrator what he took care of the taxes, and books, and the tenants to collect tax-- I mean, the rent.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And his name was Auerbach, Milo Auerbach.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then we had also a house-- woman, which is they call a [POLISH] in Polish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But is like-- I think in English it's more like a housekeeper, outside, to keep clean, and to keep the light, the door-- the check for the tenants.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we had-- and also a sleeping and maid, which she stayed with us [INAUDIBLE] and at home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And our pride was the name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The name was-- I owe this my parents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I'm telling this to the world, to verify they were just wonderful, great human beings, not just a-- not just a statistic or a number.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that was we were proud of the name, like a crown on their heads, which they was crushed and turned to ashes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And what hurts the most-- that without scruples-- you know, too many coming already up, denying that this tragedy and Holocaust exists.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I've--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then we had-- I was-- we used to go on vacation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had the wonderful-- and we taught-- my parents taught us music.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I played mandolin.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my-- there was tutor, which told us-- my Daddy spoke five languages.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was Hebrew, Jewish, Polish, German, and Russia-- Russian language.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Hebrew-- the Bible, he translated with every-- like, if you know what the-- the Torah has the Hebrew, and the dots, he was able to transfer every dot, the meaning of it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was very knowledgeable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So was-- my mom was very intelligent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My sister was very bright.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
